I thought you were gay.

04:06.248 --> 04:10.246
Oh, I am. It's just, I play
so many heterosexual roles...

04:10.336 --> 04:14.203
I feel I really need to
do some serious research.

04:15.382 --> 04:17.255
Mm-hmm.

04:17.343 --> 04:19.418
And just when you think
there's no greater depth...

04:19.512 --> 04:21.588
to which an actor could possibly sink.

04:21.680 --> 04:25.595
- That's nothin'. Remember Fred?
- Fred.

04:25.684 --> 04:28.010
I've got a 50 percent
hearing loss in this ear...

04:28.103 --> 04:31.307
from him yelling "Stella" in bed.

04:31.398 --> 04:34.269
I tell ya, I swore
off actors a year ago.

04:34.360 --> 04:37.479
I said if that's the only
subspecies of men available...

04:37.571 --> 04:39.813
I'd rather not date at all.

04:39.907 --> 04:42.398
And I haven't. But
there are other things.

04:42.493 --> 04:46.621
My work, I perfect my craft.
L... Kor... Korzenowski!

04:46.705 --> 04:49.955
- Yeah.
- He's taking students.

04:50.042 --> 04:53.577
- Hey, but where you gonna get that kind of money?
- L...

04:53.671 --> 04:57.205
I gotta use that phone.
Come on. You're up.

05:03.389 --> 05:05.465
Who is it?

05:05.558 --> 05:08.677
It's your sister-in-law. Hurry
up. My feet are falling off.

05:08.769 --> 05:11.687
Well, hi, Shirley.
I'm glad you finally...

05:11.772 --> 05:13.848
Wait a minute.

05:13.941 --> 05:17.061
Get in front of the camera.

05:22.366 --> 05:25.320
- I knew it.
- Come on, Mom. Let me in.

05:25.411 --> 05:28.412
No, we can't afford it.

05:28.497 --> 05:30.573
Mom, please.

05:30.666 --> 05:32.742
- Is that my baby?
- Daddy!

05:32.835 --> 05:35.955
Yes, but she can't come
in. She wants a loan.

05:36.046 --> 05:38.122
Daddy, can I come in, please?

05:38.215 --> 05:40.920
Please, please, please,
please, please, Daddy? Daddy?

05:41.010 --> 05:43.086
- Daniel, what are you doing?
- Oh, yes.

05:43.179 --> 05:46.096
- You don't know she wants money.
- Of course she does.

05:46.182 --> 05:49.515
- You don't know that.
- That's right, Mom.

05:49.602 --> 05:53.516
Can't I just drop in to see my parents?

05:56.483 --> 05:58.772
Okay, I need $5,000.

05:58.861 --> 06:01.778
- But it's to study with Korzenowski. -
$5,000. - She might have a good reason.

06:01.864 --> 06:05.612
- Daddy! Stanislav Korzenowski.
- $5,000, Daniel.

06:05.701 --> 06:08.192
- I'll pay you back.
- What did you say?

06:08.287 --> 06:10.363
W
- What was that?

06:11.916 --> 06:16.993
- I know I owe you some money.
- You owe us $3 2,000.

06:17.087 --> 06:19.923
But it's the Korzenowski.

06:20.007 --> 06:24.384
Lauren, we sent you to Yale
and London and the institute.

06:24.470 --> 06:28.337
You have been at this acting thing for
years, and you haven't earned a dime.

06:28.432 --> 06:30.508
You are still working as a salesgirl!

06:30.601 --> 06:33.602
- Honey, face it. Maybe it's time for you to give it up.
- Daddy.

06:33.687 --> 06:36.178
- Daniel. Hey, what did you
do? - Oh. Oh, Daddy. - Nothing.

06:36.273 --> 06:38.764
- You gave her that money? - Oh, Daddy.
- I cannot believe that you did that.

06:38.859 --> 06:42.311
- She is our only child. - Oh. Oh, Daddy!
- I can't believe it. She is sucking us dry.

06:42.404 --> 06:45.524
- $5,000. Thank you, Daddy!
- She isn't. Well, I just got another bill from Bloomingdale's.

06:45.616 --> 06:47.692
- Oh, thank you.
- Drop that now. Don't you dare start talking about that.

06:50.704 --> 06:54.453
Give me back my fuckin' quarter! Damn!

06:55.751 --> 06:57.827
Well, good luck.

07:08.138 --> 07:09.798
I'm Lauren Ames.

07:09.890 --> 07:12.179
There's my application,
your board, your pen.

07:12.268 --> 07:15.269
- Thank you.
- And my down payment.

07:15.354 --> 07:18.438
Keep that for now. You
still have to audition.

07:18.524 --> 07:21.015
- Right.
- Sit down. Mr Korzenowski will call you.

07:21.110 --> 07:23.186
Thank you.

07:29.952 --> 07:32.241
You nervous? Sorry. I'm sorry.

07:32.329 --> 07:36.078
- I mean, I'm sorry.
- It's okay. It's okay. No, I'm... I'm not... It's fine.

07:36.166 --> 07:38.539
I guess we're all a little bit, uh...

07:38.627 --> 07:40.834
Don't talk. Right.

07:40.921 --> 07:43.412
Oh, boy. I don't blame you.

07:44.884 --> 07:47.505
This is so intense. Shut up, Weldon.

07:47.595 --> 07:50.465
- I'm sorry. Sorry.
- Holy Mary!

07:50.556 --> 07:53.889
Isn't there one fucking phone
in this whole town that works?

07:55.311 --> 07:57.387
You got a phone I can use?

08:06.614 --> 08:09.947
Yeah, hi. This is Sandy
Brozinsky. Who's this?

08:10.034 --> 08:14.281
Howie. Okay, Howie. I'm holding
in my hand this thingee...

08:14.371 --> 08:16.862
says you're gonna turn
off my phone at noon.

08:16.957 --> 08:18.997
Oh, yeah? Well, I wanna
tell you somethin'.

08:19.084 --> 08:20.958
I just got out of the hospital.

08:21.045 --> 08:23.121
I get home after two
months of intensive care...

08:23.214 --> 08:26.547
they wheel me into my
building, I open my mailbox...

08:26.634 --> 08:31.212
I find your thingee screaming at
me I have till 12 noon today...

08:31.305 --> 08:33.712
Hey, no, you listen. You listen!

08:33.807 --> 08:36.927
I just opened the damn thing. I just
now laid eyes on it for the first time.

08:38.770 --> 08:40.431
What was I supposed to do?

08:40.523 --> 08:43.856
Have 'em unhook the life-support
machine so I could pay my bills?

08:45.528 --> 08:49.691
Oh, really? Yeah, so now I have
three... No, make that two minutes...

08:49.782 --> 08:52.487
to write a check and wheel
myself down to your office?

08:52.576 --> 08:54.652
Howie, is that the drill?

09:00.000 --> 09:02.289
24 hours?

09:02.378 --> 09:04.536
24 big ones?

09:04.630 --> 09:07.121
All right, Howie. You're
a prince among men.

09:07.216 --> 09:09.588
I mean it. I wanna have your child.

09:09.677 --> 09:11.135
Yeah, bye.

09:16.016 --> 09:18.305
No, stop!

09:19.395 --> 09:23.558
Please, do not screech at anyone else.

09:25.818 --> 09:28.225
I am trying to prepare
for an audition here.

09:28.320 --> 09:30.396
Thank you.

09:30.489 --> 09:32.731
Oh, yeah? What for?

09:32.825 --> 09:35.742
A workshop with Stanislav Korzenowski.

09:35.828 --> 09:38.283
Who's that?

09:38.372 --> 09:41.373
Only one of the great
geniuses of the theatre.

09:41.458 --> 09:43.617
Now if you don't mind.

09:43.711 --> 09:46.914
Hey, maybe I should audition
for him too. I'm an actress.

09:49.800 --> 09:52.884
Hey, no, I'm a pro. I bet
I'm more of a pro than you.

09:55.389 --> 10:00.181
Uh-huh. Well, I just made
2,500 bucks doin' a movie, yeah.

10:00.269 --> 10:03.887
That's where I've seen you.
It has been driving me crazy.

10:03.981 --> 10:08.524
- You saw Ninja Vixens?
- I, uh, must have.

10:08.611 --> 10:11.730
Huh. Well, this whole acting
thing's been goin' pretty good.

10:11.822 --> 10:14.693
I mean, it's all just
bullshittin', right?

10:16.118 --> 10:18.526
Actors are just
bullshitters who get paid.

10:18.621 --> 10:20.697
Where do I sign up?

10:22.291 --> 10:25.411
Just exactly what do you think
you're going to do in there?

10:25.502 --> 10:28.420
I don't know. I'll make somethin' up.

10:28.505 --> 10:32.455
You're going in to Stanislav
Korzenowski and wing it?

10:33.677 --> 10:36.168
Jesus, you'd think I was
gonna go in and pee on him.

10:38.015 --> 10:40.091
Listen to me.

10:40.184 --> 10:44.134
You do not audition for a man
of Korzenowski's reputation...

10:44.230 --> 10:46.306
without a prepared classical monologue.

10:46.398 --> 10:48.605
That means Shaw, Ibsen, Shakespeare.

10:48.692 --> 10:52.227
I'm doing Ophelia's mad scene. I'm
not waltzing in off the street...

10:52.321 --> 10:55.856
saying, "Gee, I think
I wanna be an actress."

10:56.992 --> 10:59.068
You know what I bet?

10:59.161 --> 11:02.079
I bet you haven't been
laid in about a year.

11:06.377 --> 11:09.710
- Ames, Lauren.
- Ah, ah.

11:09.797 --> 11:12.917
Yes, I'm coming. I'm...
I'm... I will be co...

11:13.008 --> 11:15.962
I'm... I'm... I'm ready. I'm... I'm...

11:16.053 --> 11:18.971
- I'm ready.
- Quickly, Miss Ames.

11:19.056 --> 11:21.547
I have a good mad scene.

11:22.184 --> 11:24.806
It's really great. I just saw it.

11:24.895 --> 11:26.971
Hmm.

11:53.174 --> 11:58.381
I will not only wish you to
absorb everything that I say.

11:58.471 --> 12:03.465
I will also wish you to keep
notes of everything that I say.

12:03.559 --> 12:08.351
And I will wish to look at those notes.

12:08.439 --> 12:12.816
Now if you say this
is like high school...

12:12.902 --> 12:14.978
I do not apologize.

12:17.072 --> 12:19.148
I am an old egotist...

12:19.241 --> 12:22.693
and I want to know that
you record my ideas.

12:23.746 --> 12:27.281
If you do not, you're
gone from the class.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.076
All right. We begin.

12:30.169 --> 12:35.127
We begin with vowel groups.

12:35.216 --> 12:37.707
Vowel groups.

12:38.761 --> 12:40.837
Mr Weldon...

12:41.889 --> 12:45.887
do you know the difference
between a Texas diphthong...

12:45.976 --> 12:48.467
and a Georgia diphthong?

12:50.189 --> 12:51.600
Sorry I'm late.

12:51.690 --> 12:55.902
They made me fill out all these
dumb-ass financial aid forms.

12:55.986 --> 12:57.112
You want 'em?

12:57.112 --> 12:57.646
You want 'em?

12:57.738 --> 13:00.858
I cannot believe... I absolutely
cannot believe he let her in!

13:00.950 --> 13:03.026
And on scholarship!

13:03.118 --> 13:06.036
I just bet I know what
she did as an audition.

13:07.081 --> 13:10.082
The woman has no
training, no experience.

13:10.167 --> 13:12.041
I mean, correct me if I'm wrong.

13:12.127 --> 13:14.416
I really thought if you
worked at your craft, maybe...

13:14.505 --> 13:16.794
just possibly, you'd get to
work with one of the greats.

13:16.882 --> 13:20.631
It's $2.95, not $295.

13:20.719 --> 13:22.795
I knew that.

13:25.474 --> 13:29.057
Something's seriously
wrong with my life.

13:29.144 --> 13:31.470
Excuse me.

13:33.524 --> 13:36.774
- Are you all right?
- Better.

13:39.113 --> 13:41.070
L-I w... I was just, um...

13:41.156 --> 13:43.233
- Who cares? May I help you?
- Yeah.

13:43.325 --> 13:47.109
- Have you got something in a pumpkin?
- The shade pumpkin?

13:47.204 --> 13:50.490
- No, a pumpkin costume.
- Oh.

13:50.583 --> 13:52.659
God, I sound like an idiot.

13:52.751 --> 13:54.827
The reason is that I
teach grammar school.

13:54.920 --> 13:57.079
- You're a
schoolteacher? - Uh-huh.

13:57.172 --> 13:59.960
- You're not an actor?
- Oh, God, no. I'd be awful.

14:00.050 --> 14:01.924
Why do you ask?

14:02.011 --> 14:05.462
Oh, well, there's just so many
actors who come in here. Please go on.

14:05.556 --> 14:07.632
Well, we're putting
on a little pageant...

14:07.725 --> 14:10.476
and there's a kid in my
class who's very insecure.

14:10.561 --> 14:12.968
You know, the other kids pick on
him and his mother doesn't sew...

14:13.063 --> 14:15.139
and I think it would
give him such a boost...

14:15.232 --> 14:17.521
to have the best darn
costume in the place.

14:17.610 --> 14:22.236
So I thought a professional costumers
would have an incredible pumpkin.

14:23.282 --> 14:25.358
But I can't go more than $50...

14:25.451 --> 14:27.739
because this is coming
out of my own pocket.

14:30.539 --> 14:33.291
I'm really sorry. I don't
think we have a pumpkin.

14:34.877 --> 14:37.415
What about a squash?

14:37.504 --> 14:40.624
We don't have any vegetables as such.

14:41.383 --> 14:43.257
I'm sorry.

14:43.344 --> 14:45.835
Well, this is the
last place on the list.

14:47.014 --> 14:50.679
But I'll just throw something
together myself, huh?

14:50.768 --> 14:53.341
I really appreciate your time. Thanks.

14:53.437 --> 14:57.304
Um, uh, listen. I don't know,
maybe, uh, maybe someone...

14:57.399 --> 15:01.527
Maybe I could, uh... I've
made a lot of my own costumes.

15:01.612 --> 15:05.859
I'm sure it wouldn't be that
difficult. If I could help out, I'd...

15:05.950 --> 15:08.026
like to.

15:08.118 --> 15:10.325
That would be fabulous.

15:21.006 --> 15:23.628
- I hope you'll forgive me, Lauren.
- For what?

15:23.717 --> 15:26.837
L... I don't usually
lunge at women like that.

15:26.929 --> 15:29.764
- Oh.
- But you just, uh...

15:32.351 --> 15:34.640
I just had to kiss you.

15:34.728 --> 15:37.848
L-I really am sorry and I hope
that you'll want to see me again.

15:37.940 --> 15:42.187
Oh, where in the world
did you come from?

15:42.278 --> 15:45.812
- New Mexico, originally.
- No, no, I mean...

15:45.906 --> 15:48.195
how can a man so delightful as you...

15:48.284 --> 15:52.447
be just wandering the
streets of New York?

15:52.538 --> 15:55.658
Single, single, yeah.
I can't believe it.

15:55.749 --> 15:58.916
Well, that's not by choice.
I'd like to be married.

15:59.962 --> 16:03.331
- This isn't happening.
- Why not?

16:03.424 --> 16:06.757
Well, there must be something wrong
with you. Don't you have any faults?

16:08.554 --> 16:11.045
I smoke.

16:12.308 --> 16:15.558
You smoke? That's it? Call the police!

16:15.644 --> 16:19.179
No, no, no. It's an addiction.

16:19.273 --> 16:23.223
Colton's tobacco. New Mexico's finest.

16:23.319 --> 16:25.810
I hope you don't mind.

16:25.905 --> 16:29.819
Well, I'll struggle through somehow.

16:31.744 --> 16:33.617
Good. Very good.

16:33.704 --> 16:36.824
Because, uh, I'd like
to see you again...

16:38.542 --> 16:40.618
tomorrow night.

16:42.588 --> 16:44.664
Well, yes.

16:54.642 --> 16:57.346
Mmm, thank you.

17:01.732 --> 17:04.436
What's this?

17:04.526 --> 17:09.319
"Ooh, eee, ooh, ah, ooh, eee, ah, ooh."

17:09.406 --> 17:12.359
- That's what you do in acting class?
- Those are vowel groups.

17:12.451 --> 17:16.496
Mmm, sorry. "Wowel" groups.

17:16.579 --> 17:18.537
- Ooh. -
Ooh. - Ooh.

17:18.624 --> 17:21.790
- Ooh, I feel the same way.
- Ooh, ooh.

17:21.877 --> 17:24.997
Will you please kiss
me hard on the lips?

17:27.174 --> 17:29.665
That was tender, but tasty.

17:29.760 --> 17:32.251
- Bite my face.
- Okay.

17:33.848 --> 17:38.011
Bite my leg. Now bite my other leg.

17:41.272 --> 17:44.605
- You get her two 1 X legs and...
- Going over the fence gymnastics?

17:44.692 --> 17:46.980
Oh, oh, I'm sorry.

17:48.237 --> 17:51.688
Oh, my. That kind of evening, huh?

17:54.285 --> 17:58.069
Not the kind you're used
to. No money changed hands.

18:08.674 --> 18:11.379
No, no, no, no. Reveal, reveal.

18:11.468 --> 18:14.802
You have killed your father.
You have married your mother.

18:14.889 --> 18:17.380
Na, no words, remember.

18:18.434 --> 18:20.307
Na, reveal.

18:29.653 --> 18:32.939
Here we have a sick sea lion. Go.

18:34.867 --> 18:38.318
- Miss Brozinsky.
- Okay.

18:38.412 --> 18:42.362
You will now perform for
us, also without words...

18:42.458 --> 18:45.031
Hamlet's soliloquy.

18:46.212 --> 18:48.619
Who's that?

18:48.714 --> 18:50.790
Hamlet.

18:52.343 --> 18:54.419
Hamlet.

18:55.888 --> 18:58.758
Shakespeare's tragedy of Hamlet.

19:02.770 --> 19:05.343
Ah, well.

19:05.439 --> 19:08.559
Uh, for her, we get the comic book, huh?

19:16.200 --> 19:18.869
Taxi!

19:18.953 --> 19:20.826
Hey!

19:30.631 --> 19:32.090
Hey!

19:32.174 --> 19:35.958
Oh. Ooh, that creep
Korzenowski is driving me nuts.

19:36.053 --> 19:38.295
Ooh.

19:38.389 --> 19:41.390
I know what I need.

19:48.065 --> 19:50.983
Oh, God!

19:51.068 --> 19:53.144
Oh, God!

19:53.237 --> 19:56.154
Oh, God! Oh, God!

19:56.240 --> 19:58.114
Oh, God!

19:58.200 --> 20:02.743
Oh, God! Oh, God!

20:02.830 --> 20:04.906
Ooh.

20:11.714 --> 20:14.833
To die on the stage...

20:16.260 --> 20:19.795
is perhaps the greatest
single challenge...

20:19.889 --> 20:22.380
an actor can face.

20:25.477 --> 20:29.855
The audience must know,
must absolutely believe...

20:29.940 --> 20:32.645
that the breath, that the very life...

20:32.735 --> 20:35.142
is going out of your body.

20:35.237 --> 20:37.313
Now...

20:37.406 --> 20:41.653
You! You will die now, please.

20:42.494 --> 20:45.448
No, no, I don't believe you.

20:47.333 --> 20:51.081
Maintain your focus.
Na, I don't believe you.

20:51.170 --> 20:55.796
- Maintain your focus and lean forward.
- Stop, stop, stop. Stop it. Stop it.

20:59.553 --> 21:02.388
- Are you all right?
- Fine.

21:06.977 --> 21:11.057
Perhaps you would like to
